        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28229",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "You *can* specify the 'multiple' option via the $attribs array (third argument):\n\n{code}\n$this->formSelect('foo', '', array('multiple' => 'multiple'));\n{code}\n\nHowever, this implicitly adds the array notation ('[]') to the element name when you do. The rationale is that ZF will not be able to handle the submitted values if the array notation is not in place. I consider it a fringe case that you would _not_ want this, and feel the code to support it would introduce undue complexity to the helper.\n\nIf you do not want this behavior, override the FormSelect view helper by extending it locally and ensuring that your helper prefix is registered.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-15T04:41:00.000+0000",
